### <a id="beta-1"></a> 2.7 Beta 1

* **[Feature]** You can download a ZIP file containing various diagnostic files using the Ops Manager API or UI. For more information, see [Support Bundle](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-7/opsman-api/#support-bundle) in the Ops Manager API documentation. To access the support bundle using the UI, click **Support** in the footer of Ops Manager. New API endpoints for diagnostics, Ops Manager logs, and apply changes logs support this feature. 
* **[Feature]** You can see all Ops Manager root and NATS certificate authorities (CAs) in the deployed certificates endpoint. For more information, see [Listing the Root Certificate Authorities](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-7/opsman-api/#listing-the-root-certificate-authorities) in the Ops Manager API documentation.
* **[Feature]** Ops Manager sanitizes new line characters in certificates in a consistent way so that VMs are not recreated unnecessarily when certificates are submitted within the UI or the API.
* **[Features]** When an input value violate constraints for jobs configured on the **Resource Config**
pane, Ops Manager highlights the associated `Instances`, `VM types`, and `Persistent Disk Types`
fields and displays an explanatory error messages about the violation.

