### <a id="alpha-3"></a> 2.7 Alpha 3

* **[Feature]** Ops Managers now verifies cron expressions for tiles that require them for scheduling backups. See [Valid cron Input Verification](#cron) below.
* **[Feature]** For vSphere users, NSX-V and NSX-T are now configurable in the the **Resource Config** pane of the BOSH Director tile. Properties for NSX-V are: Security groups and lbs. Properties for NSX-T are: ns groups, vif type, and lb.
* **[Feature]** The Ops Manager **Resource Config** UI has improved error handling. When there is an error, Ops Manager displays both a banner and an error message next to the field containing the error. 
* **[Feature]** The `/api/v0/deployed/certificates` now displays the Ops Manager root and NATS CAs 
* **[Feature]** This alpha release features additional changes from the redesign of the **Resource Config** pane. 
* **[Feature]** As part of the redesign of the **Resource Config** pane, the **Load Balancer** and **Internet Connected** fields are now under a dropdown menu.
* **[Feature]** On OpenStack, operators can assign floating IP addresses to Ops Manager jobs.
* **[Feature]** Users can now see all CredHub managed certificates from `/api/v0/deployed/certificates`
* **[Breaking Change]** CredHub managed certificates returned from `/api/v0/deployed/certificates` do not contain the `valid_from` and `issuer` fields. 



